President Joseph R. Biden has declared a major disaster for the Oglala Sioux Tribe due to severe winter storms and snowstorms that occurred from December 12 to December 25, 2022. The declaration allows for federal assistance to supplement the tribe's efforts in the affected areas. Federal funding will be available on a cost-sharing basis for emergency work, repair or replacement of damaged facilities, snow assistance for a continuous 48-hour period, and hazard mitigation measures. Alana B. Kuhn has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for recovery operations, and additional designations may be made based on further damage assessments. For more information, media can contact the FEMA news desk.